args: The heck is up with these guys?!\nWhy do they keep targeting you?!
Maybe my new armor just stands out!
This is no time for jokes, idiot!\nYou're surrounded!
Don't worryâ€”my armor can handle it!
Their attacks ain't even gonna scratch it!
Crap, Ranzal. I can't believe how many\nof 'em you just took out.
With this new sword and armor,\nthey didn't stand a chance!
Is it just me, or are you moving faster\nthan you did before?
Is that armor lighter or something?
If anything, it's a bit heavier.
Then why are you faster now?
Partially because this was specially\ncrafted for me, I think.
But also because of muscle power!
When armor's heavy, ya gotta bulk up\nso ya don't get all sluggish, yeah?
I totally do not follow you.
Well, I AM faster, right?\nSo my muscles musta leveled-up!
And I'm gonna keep trainin' until they're\nthe most muscly muscles they can be!
Look, I know you've got new armor and all,\nbut don't you think you're getting a bit\nTOO gung-ho here?
Nah, this is how it should be.\nI'm gonna be reborn!
Before we met, I lived as a mercenary.
I did whatever it took to win.
I'm too ashamed to even talk about\nsome'a the stuff what I done.
Yeah, but isn't that just what a\nmercenary has to do?
Sureâ€”but that kind of underhanded\nstrength is somethin' I wanna get\naway from in my new life.
There's only one way to get real strength,\nand that's to train like a madman.
It's like bein' on a hill. If ya wanna reach\nthe top, ya just gotta keep walkin'.
So that's what I'm gonna do.
And someday, I'll be reborn with good,\nhonest strength that fits my new role\nin the world.
You sound like a real leader!
I always used to see you as my dumb pal,\nbut now it's like you're...shining.
Nothin' shines brighter than a guy\nworkin' to better himself.
I wanna be just like you!
How can I be the next Ranzal?
Train well, eat well, and sleep well.
I'm gonna get on that right away!\n...Speaking of, I'm kinda hungry.
No surprise; we worked hard today.\nLet's get back to the castle, yeah?
I bet Cleo's got grub waitin' for us.
I think the eating is going to be my\nfavorite part of your big three.
I'm sorry, but the food isn't ready.
Yes, I know it's terribly disappointing.\nIf you are going to keel over, try not\nto do so on my clean floor.
No snacking! I must ensure that everyone\ngets a fair and equal portion.
So if you eat so much as a bite,\nthat is ALL you will have today!
But we been fightin' fiends all day!
Any further interruptions will simply\ndelay everyone's food.
Oh, for the goddess's sake! Are you FIVE?!\nI thought you had grown up, Ranzal,\nbut perhaps I was mistaken.
What happened to the man dreaming of\ngood, honest strength? What happened\nto the guy I wanted to be like?
